model_explanation: S2 is stating something about Sue, while S1 focuses on Rob, so they are independent statements and do not directly relate to each other in an entailment or contradiction.
the focus in S1 is on Sue and the fact that only grapes were given, so S2 directly contradicts that by introducing another item (oranges) given to Sue.
if Sam only gave Sue grapes, then it’s entailed by S1 that Sam did not give Sue bananas.
S1 is about Mary only receiving grapes, while S2 discusses Ellen also receiving grapes. There’s no direct entailment or contradiction between what was said about Mary and what was said about Ellen.
if Sam only gave Rob oranges, then giving Rob bananas contradicts the statement.
if the only thing Sam gave Sue was bananas, it entails that grapes were not given.

if Sam only gave Tom bananas, it entails that grapes were not given to Tom.
